SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1102
By Roberts
A RESOLUTION to honor Billy Vogle on his exemplary tenure as
Robertson County Mayor.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those Tennesseans who have performed with uncommon devotion and ability
throughout their careers in public service; and
WHEREAS, one such outstanding person is outgoing Robertson County Mayor Billy
Vogle, who is taking a well-earned retirement from public office in 2026 after a distinguished
career that has spanned twenty-eight years; and
WHEREAS, Billy Vogle first served as a valuable member of the Robertson County
Commission for twenty years (1998-2018) before being elected county mayor; and
WHEREAS, in this role, he contributed significantly to the commission's Budget
Committee, Education Committee, Landfill Committee, Law Enforcement Committee, and
Nominating Committee; and
WHEREAS, in 2018, Billy Vogle sought the office of Robertson County Mayor and was
elected; he has served with distinction for the past eight years, playing an important role in the
growth and prosperity of the county and the Middle Tennessee region; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Vogle has worked with elected officials, community leaders, and
citizens to shape Robertson County's future while protecting its character and sense of
community; and
WHEREAS, he has effectively preserved and advanced the collective interests of the
citizens of Robertson County during his tenure; and
SJR1102
016590
- 1 -

WHEREAS, on the professional level, Mayor Vogle is a man of many talents; he is a
small business owner and farmer in Adams and previously served as President of Tobacco
Pride, Inc.; and
WHEREAS, he has also worked for the Adams/Cedar Hill Water Plant and L&N/CSX
Railroad; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Vogle practices his faith as a member of Adams United Methodist
Church and gives back to his community as a member of Red River Lodge 537, where he is a
three-time past Master; and
WHEREAS, a devoted family man, Billy Vogle is most grateful for the love and support
of his wife of fifty years, Cindy Vogle; children, Jill (Dustin) York, Will Vogle, and Matt (Megan)
Vogle; and grandchildren, Carter and Kinley York, Johnnie and Annie Vogle, and Carter and
Charlie Vogle; and
WHEREAS, by not seeking reelection in 2026, Mayor Vogle is concluding a remarkable
career spent in dedicated service to the good people of Robertson County; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Billy Vogle is most deserving of our approbation on this special
occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Billy Vogle on his exemplary tenure as
Robertson County Mayor, salute his ongoing commitment to his community and its progress,
and extend to him our best wishes for a happy and fulfilling retirement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
